100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 7, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, focusing on global disarmament amid rising tensions in Europe. In the United States, the ongoing Scopes Trial continued to capture national attention, spotlighting the clash between science and religion in education. Meanwhile, rising inflation in Germany was causing widespread economic distress as the country struggled to recover from the aftermath of World War I.
